<div class="app-card-container">
      <div class="card">
    <h1>About Me</h1>

    <hr>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <%= image_tag "Justin_Kinner_Developer_Pic_edited.jpg", width:300, alt: "profile image" %> 
        <div> <h3> Time per skill in Month </h3> </div>
        <div class="skills">
          <% @skills.each do |skill|%>
            <div class="skill">
              <h4><%= skill.title %></h4>
              <div class="progress">
                <div 
                  class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped bg-warning"
                  role="progressbar"
                  aria-valuenow="<%= skill.percent_utilized %>"
                  aria-valuemax="100"
                  style="width: <%= skill.percent_utilized %>%"
                ></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
       
      <div class="col-md-8">
      <p>After over a decade of business experience, an MBA and working in varied companies and startups in a number of industries, I realized I was never fully content with the creation options available to me. It wasn't until I came up software and web development, later in my career, that I found my true passion. In this industry I can tie together all the things that I love about working with people and the creation process. It is a great time to creating.</p>

      <p>It is my mission to provide quality projects, grow my skills and help better the companies and teams I work for and with. When developing projects for customers and teams, I take a hands on approach and attempt to be transparent every step of the way. I love to utilize the newest technologies and learn new things. Let's work together and build some amazing products!</p>

        <p>
          <button 
            class="btn btn-primary"
            type="button"
            data-toggle="collapse"
            data-target="#jobHistory"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controler="jobHistory"
          >
            Recent Job History
          </button>

          <button 
            class="btn btn-primary"
            type="button"
            data-toggle="collapse"
            data-target="#education"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controler="education"
          >
            Education
          </button>

